{"lemma":"نَجِسَ","slug":"نَجِسَ","root":"ن.ج.س","root_slug":"ن-ج-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ج-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَجَس","root":"نجس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39431"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be unclean, to be impure"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to defile, to besmirch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَجِسَ (najisa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"filth, impurity"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unclean, impure"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"irremediable"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39431","headword_ar":"نَجِسَ","root":"njs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najasa","text_ar":"نَجَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najusa","text_ar":"نَجُسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) accord. to some, but the books of good repute are silent respecting this last; (Msb;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najasN","text_ar":"نَجَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) of the first; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najaAsapN","text_ar":"نَجَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or this last is a simple subst. [as the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najusa","text_ar":"نَجُسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to which by rule it should belong is not of good authority]; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, unclean, dirty, filthy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahara","text_ar":"طَهَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahura","text_ar":"طَهُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K: *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najaAsap","text_ar":"نَجَاسَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of two kinds; one kind is perceived by sense; and one kind is perceived by the mind; of which latter kind is that which is attributed, in the Kur, ix. 28, to those who assert God to have associates: (Er-Rághib, B:) but in this latter sense, it is said by Z, to be tropical. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najaAsapN","text_ar":"نَجَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] You also say, (of a garment, A, Msb,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnj~s","text_ar":"تنجّس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rendered unclean, dirty, filthy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najosN","text_ar":"نَجْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. an inf. n. of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najasa","text_ar":"نَجَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a child's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euwdap","text_ar":"عُودَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amulet, of any of the kinds described below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanojiysN","text_ar":"تَنْجِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","Msb","TA"]}]}}